                    "company": "ASML",
                    "description": "In this role, I was responsible for ASML's 30th anniversary ('ASML30'\u200b) in 2014. Managing a 3.5M Euro budget and a team of 4 FTE in our corporate HQ in The Netherlands, I designed and lead a global program that celebrated the heart and soul of the company through 3 key themes: Our Story, Our Diversity and Our Responsibility.\n\nKey accomplishments:\n- 'Our Stories'\u200b, a series of short interviews on film with employees in locations worldwide. We published to YouTube, one every two weeks. Absolute highlight was interviewing the esteemed Gordon Moore!\n- 'Sharing Dishes'\u200b, a book with dishes shared by employees from all over the world, in celebration of the cultural diversity within our company.\n- '30 For Change'\u200b, raising funds for 30 charity projects related to education in developing nations. Each charity project was submitted and championed by an employee.\n- 'ASML Festival'\u200b, a final celebration of our 30 year anniversary in which all projects, initiatives and themes came together. The event drew 10,000 employees and their partners to the Brabanthallen.\n- 'Diversity In The Park', a 5-day music and cultural festival on our campus in celebrate our cultural diversity. Employee groups decorated stalls to share their cultural heritage with colleagues.",
