                    "company": "ASML",
                    "description": "In this dual role, I was responsible for the employee engagement program (internal communications) and sponsoring program (corporate communications). \n\nConnecting these two areas of expertise whenever possible, I created a high impact mix of corporate social responsibility and proud, motivated, inspired employees in support of ASML's vision as a place to work, meet, share and learn.\n\nKey accomplishments:\n- Launched ASML's first (2009) and second (2011) worldwide employee surveys, measuring key metrics on engagement, satisfaction and employee experience. The surveys had solid response rates of 59% (2009) and 85% (2011) and lead to global improvement initiatives, executed by HR.\n- Integrated key sponsorships with employee engagement program: became strategic partner to Muziekgebouw Eindhoven (rolled out music program tailored to our employees), partner to hockey club Oranje-Zwart Eindhoven (organized hockey clinic day for 200+ kids of employees), partner to Marathon Eindhoven (activating 500+ employees to participate in the running event)\n- Designed and implemented digital solutions to bridge the global gap between ASML\u2019s 70 offices. Examples include launching Yammer and a corporate television concept branded \u2018@ASML\u2019\n- Co-founded Young ASML, the platform to develop, connect and support our young professionals. The platform organized 12 impactful events and grew to 500 members in its first year.",
